ameron Mackintosh. Adapted by iTheatrics under the supervision of Timothy Allen McDonald. <span class=\"ItalicText\">Mary Poppins JR.</span> is directed by Katlyn Redding.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Advanced Glee (Saturday class)</span> presents <span class=\"BoldText\">Lionel Bart’s <span class=\"ItalicText\">Oliver! JR.</span></span>  Consider yourself at home with <span class=\"ItalicText\">Oliver! JR.</span>, the Broadway Junior version of Lionel Bart's classic musical based on Charles Dickens' novel, Oliver Twist. The streets of Victorian England come to life as Oliver, a malnourished orphan in a workhouse, becomes the neglected apprentice of an undertaker. Oliver escapes to London and finds acceptance amongst a group of petty thieves and pickpockets led by the elderly Fagin. However, being captured for a theft that he did not commit, Oliver’s chances of discovering the true love of a family is threatened. <span class=\"ItalicText\">Oliver! JR.</span> is full of classic songs like \"Consider Yourself\", \"Food Glorious Food\", and \"Oom-Pah-Pah.\" Book, Music and Lyrics by Lionel Bart. <span class=\"ItalicText\">Oliver! JR.</span> is directed by Karen Rose with assistance from Vamshi Vakulabharanam.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">MARY POPPINS JR and LIONEL BARTS OLIVER! JR are both presented through special arrangement with Music Theatre International (MTI). All authorized performance materials are also supplied by MTI.  The video or audio recording of these productions is strictly prohibited.</span>  <span><br/></span><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://www.mtishows.com/\">www.mtishows.com</a>  <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Learn more about the University of Regina Conservatory of Performing Arts and about joining Summer Creative Camps in July & August or our Musical Theatre & Drama programs in the fall of 2026:  <span><br/></span><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://www.uregina.ca/academics/continuing-education/conservatory-of-performing-arts.html\"> Conservatory of Performing Arts</a><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">Tickets are $16.80 in advance and $21.00 at the door, inclusive of fees and taxes.  Seating is not assigned.</span>
""";
