<http://www.spektrix.com/darkehallsociety/event/35001ANDBMVNTNMQTQBCTTLTMVTJHVKBV>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Stream of Dance Festival - SDFest #2";
  schema:description """
	<span class=\"BoldText\">SDFest #2</span> is the second performance of the <span class=\"BoldText\">Stream of Dance Festival co-presented by New Dance Horizons, Regina Musical Club, and Compagnie de la Citadelle</span>.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Set to <span class=\"BoldText\">Olivier Messiaen’s Quartet for the End of Time</span> and performed live by the musicians of <span class=\"BoldText\">CrossRoute</span>, <span class=\"ItalicText\">Contes pour la fin du temps</span> (Tales for the End of Time) explores the concept of artistic expression amidst isolation, inviting audiences to ponder the interconnectedness of circumstance and the act of creation.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Choreographed and directed by Laurence Lemieux<span><br/></span>Live Musical Performance by CrossRoute (Christian Robinson, violin; Simon Fryer, cello; Hyonsuk Kim, clarinet; Chris Kayler, piano<span><br/></span>Dancers: Morgyn Aronyk-Schell, Sierra Chin Sawdy, Miyeko Ferguson, Sully Malaeb Prouls, Connor Mitton, Claire Whitaker<span><br/></span>Music: Quatuor pour la fin du temps, by Olivier Messiaen<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Visit <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://www.newdancehorizons.ca/stream-of-dance-festival.html\">THEIR WEBSITE</a> for more information.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">Tickets are $35 for adults inclusive of fees and taxes.  Those under 18 years of age and U of R students receive free admission but are asked to book a ticket.  Seating is not assigned.</span>
""";
