<http://www.spektrix.com/darkehallsociety/event/26401ANCDKPPRRGMBPNMJGQSVPCDHQSJS>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "UofR 3 Minute Thesis Competition";
  schema:description """
	Join us for an evening of discovery, inspiration, and bold ideas at the <span class=\"BoldText\">University of Regina's Three-Minute Thesis (3MT®) Finale.</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Be part of an extraordinary evening celebrating the innovative research of our 8 graduate student finalists.  The 3MT Finale showcases the incredible ability of thesis-based students to present their complex research in just three minutes, using only one static slide.  This unique event bridges the gap between academia and the community, highlighting research that addresses real-world challenges.  From health and wellness to engineering, technology, the arts, and sport, you'll hear how innovative ideas are making an impact across a wide range of disciplines.  Each presentation highlights not only the research itself, but the passion, creativity, and communication skills of the students behind it.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Whether you're curious about new discoveries, eager to support student success, or simply looking for an engaging evening, this event offers something for everyone.  Come celebrate innovation, cheer on our graduate students, and vote for your favourite presentation in the People's Choice Award.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">This event is open to the public and free to attend.</span><span><br/></span>
""";
  schema:startDate "2026-03-26T18:00:00"^^xsd:dateTime;
